Step 1. Gross Profit Margin  
• From the income statement, Gross Profit = 6,476,677.56 and Total Revenue = 22,876,677.56.  
• Calculate:  
 Gross Profit Margin = (6,476,677.56 / 22,876,677.56) × 100 ≈ 28.33%

Step 2. Operating Cash Flow Ratio  
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -16,772,398.72  
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = Accounts Payable + Taxes Payable = 2,000,000.00 + 1,143,833.89 = 3,143,833.89  
• Calculate:  
 Operating Cash Flow Ratio = -16,772,398.72 / 3,143,833.89 ≈ -5.33

Thus, the solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "28.33%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-5.33"
  }
}
